A man has died in Kajiado town after a vehicle he was travelling in was involved in an accident with another vehicle. Witnesses said the man was in a speeding Pajero before It's driver tried to avoid hitting an on coming matatu. In the process, the private car rolled several times after it lost control in the process. The passenger was pronounced dead on arrival at Kajiado county referral hospital. His driver escaped death but came out with multiple injuries. He was also taken to the same hospital. No one in the matatu was hurt in the incident. The police towed the damaged car to Central Police Station.